SIMPLE: presbyterian
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Presbyterian
<hw>Pres`by*te"ri*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>presbyt⟦eacute⟧rien</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to a
presbyter, or to ecclesiastical government by presbyters; relating to
those who uphold church government by presbyters; also, to the doctrine,
discipline, and worship of a communion so governed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Presbyterian</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Presbyterian
<hw>Pres`by*te"ri*an</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>presbyt⟦eacute⟧rien</ets>.]</ety> <def>One who maintains the
validity of ordination and government by presbyters; a member of the
Presbyterian church.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Reformed Presbyterians</b></col>. <cd>See
<er>Cameronian</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Presbyterianism</ent>⟦br⟧
